author: Laura Stevens
title: Amazon to Deliver Whole Foods Groceries
text:
Amazon.com Inc. said it would start delivering Whole Foods groceries via its fastest delivery option in four markets, marking the first major integration between its e-commerce operations and its new brick-and-mortar grocery chain.
The online retail giant will add Whole Foods to its one- and two-hour delivery option, Prime Now, in the grocerâ€™s hometown of Austin, Texas, as well as Dallas, Virginia Beach, Va. and Cincinnati, Ohio.
